---
/**
 * Our Work. The institution's operational record: each programme, the state it
 * is in, and where the public records supporting it can be found.
 *
 * No invented projects, numbers or links. A record that does not exist yet is
 * absent from this page, not promised in a broken link.
 */
import ContentPage from '../layouts/ContentPage.astro';

/**
 * Published clothing distribution records, by year. Every entry here must
 * correspond to a real file under public/records/clothing/ — a link on this
 * page is a promise that it resolves.
 */
const clothingRecords = [
  { year: 2021, photographs: 7, newspaper: false },
  { year: 2024, photographs: 4, newspaper: true },
  { year: 2025, photographs: 4, newspaper: true },
].map(({ year, photographs, newspaper }) => ({
  year,
  items: [
    ...Array.from({ length: photographs }, (_, i) => ({
      href: `/records/clothing/${year}/distribution-${String(i + 1).padStart(2, '0')}.jpg`,
      label: `Photograph ${i + 1}`,
    })),
    ...(newspaper
      ? [
          {
            href: `/records/clothing/${year}/newspaper-01.jpg`,
            label: 'Newspaper coverage',
          },
        ]
      : []),
  ],
}));
---

<ContentPage
  title="Our Work"
  description="What the institution does, what it has completed, and where the public records supporting that work can be found."
>
  <p>
    This page records what the institution does, what it has already completed,
    and where the supporting public records can be found.
  </p>
  <p>
    The work is small and specific. It is meant to continue. Alongside the
    programmes below, the institution makes a charitable contribution each year.
  </p>

  <h2>Education</h2>
  <p class="status">Status: Ongoing</p>
  <p>
    The institution supports one child through to graduation. It meets that
    child's educational costs and the essential living needs that keep school
    possible.
  </p>

  <h2>Seasonal Clothing Distribution</h2>
  <p class="status">Status: Recurring</p>
  <p>
    Warm blankets before winter and essential clothing during summer, given to
    families in need.
  </p>
  <p>
    Larger programmes were held in 2021, 2024 and 2025. Smaller distributions
    take place between them.
  </p>
  <p>
    The institution was formally registered in February 2022. The December 2021
    distribution was community work that immediately preceded its formation and
    reflected the same mission it was established to continue.
  </p>

  <h2>Access to Public Healthcare</h2>
  <p class="status">Status: Completed</p>
  <p>
    The institution helped eligible families below the poverty line access the
    Ayushman Bharat health insurance scheme.
  </p>

  <h2>Financial Awareness</h2>
  <p class="status">Status: Completed</p>
  <p>
    The institution explained the Pradhan Mantri Jeevan Jyoti Bima Yojana
    (PMJJBY), a government life insurance scheme, to families who were eligible
    for it.
  </p>

  <h2>Educational Materials</h2>
  <p class="status">Status: Completed</p>
  <p>The institution donated books and study materials.</p>

  <h2>Public Records</h2>
  <p>
    The work above is documented by public records. The photographs and
    newspaper coverage from each clothing distribution are listed below. The
    annual report card will be published here once it has been reviewed and
    approved for release.
  </p>

  <h3>Clothing Distribution</h3>
  {
    clothingRecords.map((record) => (
      <div class="record-group">
        <h4>{record.year}</h4>
        <ul>
          {record.items.map((item) => (
            <li>
              <a href={item.href}>{item.label}</a>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
    ))
  }

  <h2>Looking Ahead</h2>
  <p>
    New work begins only when the existing commitments can continue
    responsibly. A commitment that cannot be sustained is not taken on.
  </p>
  <p>
    The current priorities are scholarships, and practical educational resources
    that are useful to the public.
  </p>
</ContentPage>

<style>
  /* The state of each programme, kept quieter than the text it labels. */
  .status {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-ink-soft);
  }

  /* A year of records, kept compact so the list reads as an index. */
  .record-group h4 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .record-group ul {
    margin-top: 0;
  }
</style>
